*gtoaster-1.0_beta6 (06 Sep 2002)

  30 Oct 2002; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org> gtoaster-1.0_beta6.ebuild,
  files/scdtosr.diff :
  Modified source code so detection of devices defaults to sr instead of
  scd.

  28 Oct 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>
  gtoaster-1.0_beta6.ebuild :
  Added app-cdr/cdrdao to DEPEND list, closing bug #9661 by
  grant.likely@gdcanada.com (Grant Likely)

  06 Sep 2002; Nick Hadaway <raker@gentoo.org>
  gtoaster-1.0_beta6.ebuild, files/digest-gtoaster-1.0_beta6 :
  Version bump.  nls additions.  recorder detection bug fix.  Burns
  faster than 24x are now possible.


*gtoaster-1.0_beta5 (28 Mar 2002)

  14 Aug 2002; Pieter Van den Abeele <pvdabeel@gentoo.org> :
  Added ppc keyword

  28 Mar 2002; Seemant Kulleen <seemant@gentoo.org>  gtoaster-1.0_beta5.ebuild :
  Changed USE flag from "ogg" to "oggvorbis"

*gtoaster-1.0_beta5 (1 Feb 2002)

  1 Feb 2002; G.Bevin <gbevin@gentoo.org> ChangeLog :
  Added initial ChangeLog which should be updated whenever the package is
  updated in any way. This changelog is targetted to users. This means that the
  comments should well explained and written in clean English. The details about
  writing correct changelogs are explained in the skel.ChangeLog file which you
  can find in the root directory of the portage repository.
